OL,3,CKiller of 9-year old Alfie Steele
OL,4,Ccan't appeal against conviction,
OL,5,Cjudges say
OL,7,FThe watchdog looked at 20 interactions
OL,8,Fbetween West Mercia Police and Alfie,
OL,9,Fhis mother and her partner between
OL,10,FMarch 2018 and February 2021, but
OL,11,Ffound that there was "no indication of
OL,12,Fmisconduct" by any individual officer.
OL,14,FThere had been a "significant amount
OL,15,Fof contact" with the force in the
OL,16,Fyears before the child died, but the
OL,17,Ffamily home had a "climate of fear"
OL,18,Fwhich meant Alfie was allegedly asleep
OL,19,Fduring the occasions the police were
OL,20,Fcalled to the property, the watchdog
OL,21,Fsaid.
